## **🖥️ Must-Know PowerShell Commands for Automation**

While you're learning, these **core commands** will be your bread and butter:

|**Command**|**What It Does**|
|---|---|
|`Get-Command`|Lists all available PowerShell commands|
|`Get-Help <cmd>`|Shows help for a command (`Get-Help Rename-Item -Examples`)|
|`Get-ChildItem`|Lists files and folders (like `ls` in Linux)|
|`Rename-Item`|Renames files and folders|
|`Move-Item`|Moves files to a new directory|
|`Copy-Item`|Copies files|
|`Remove-Item`|Deletes files (USE WITH CAUTION!)|
|`Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned`|Enables PowerShell script execution|
|`Get-Process`|Lists running processes|
|`Start-Process`|Starts a new process|
|`Stop-Process`|Kills a process|
|`Test-Path`|Checks if a file or folder exists|
|`Write-Output "Hello, PowerShell!"`|Prints text to the console|
|`Export-Csv`|Saves data to a CSV file|
|`ConvertTo-Json`|Converts objects to JSON format|
|`Measure-Object`|Measures file size, word count, etc.|

